### **Script: `scan_number.sh` — Full Forensics on a Phone Number**

This script will:
- Search SMS + call logs (if Termux API is installed)
- Crawl SD card for text references
- Search WhatsApp and other messaging folders

---

### **Step 1: Create the Script**

In Termux:

```bash
nano scan_number.sh
```

Paste this inside:

```bash
#!/data/data/com.termux/files/usr/bin/bash

# Check for number
if [ -z &quot;$1&quot; ]; then
  echo &quot;Usage: ./scan_number.sh &lt;phonenumber&gt;&quot;
  exit 1
fi

NUMBER=&quot;$1&quot;
ALT1=&quot;(${NUMBER:0:3}) ${NUMBER:3:3}-${NUMBER:6:4}&quot;
ALT2=&quot;+1$NUMBER&quot;

echo &quot;[*] Scanning for: $NUMBER | $ALT1 | $ALT2&quot;

# Check call logs
echo -e &quot;\n[*] Checking call logs:&quot;
termux-call-log | grep -i &quot;$NUMBER&quot;
termux-call-log | grep -i &quot;$ALT2&quot;

# Check SMS logs
echo -e &quot;\n[*] Checking SMS messages:&quot;
termux-sms-list | grep -i &quot;$NUMBER&quot;
termux-sms-list | grep -i &quot;$ALT2&quot;

# Build file list
echo -e &quot;\n[*] Building file list...&quot;
find /sdcard -name &quot;*.txt&quot; -o -name &quot;*.log&quot; -o -name &quot;*.json&quot; -o -name &quot;*.csv&quot; &gt; /sdcard/.scan_files.txt

echo -e &quot;\n[*] Scanning files...&quot;
cat /sdcard/.scan_files.txt | while read file; do
  grep -iH &quot;$NUMBER&quot; &quot;$file&quot; 2&gt;/dev/null &amp;&amp; echo &quot;[hit] $file&quot;
  grep -iH &quot;$ALT1&quot; &quot;$file&quot; 2&gt;/dev/null &amp;&amp; echo &quot;[hit] $file&quot;
  grep -iH &quot;$ALT2&quot; &quot;$file&quot; 2&gt;/dev/null &amp;&amp; echo &quot;[hit] $file&quot;
done

# Scan WhatsApp
echo -e &quot;\n[*] Scanning WhatsApp files...&quot;
find /sdcard/WhatsApp -type f -exec grep -iH &quot;$NUMBER&quot; {} \; 2&gt;/dev/null

echo -e &quot;\n[+] Scan complete.&quot;
```

---

### **Step 2: Save &amp; Run It**

Save and exit with `CTRL + X`, then:

```bash
chmod +x scan_number.sh
./scan_number.sh 6019372496
```

